            title: 'Complex Grammar Structures', 
            description: 'Conditionals, passive voice, reported speech',
            theory: `<h3>📚 Conditionals (Условные предложения)</h3>
            <h4>Type 0 (General truths):</h4>
            <p>If + Present Simple, Present Simple</p>
            <p><em>If you heat water to 100°C, it boils.</em></p>
            
            <h4>Type 1 (Real present/future):</h4>
            <p>If + Present Simple, will + infinitive</p>
            <p><em>If it rains, I will stay at home.</em></p>
            
            <h4>Type 2 (Unreal present):</h4>
            <p>If + Past Simple, would + infinitive</p>
            <p><em>If I had money, I would buy a car.</em></p>
            
            <h4>Type 3 (Unreal past):</h4>
            <p>If + Past Perfect, would have + V3</p>
            <p><em>If I had studied, I would have passed.</em></p>
            
            <h4>🔄 Passive Voice:</h4>
            <p>Object + be + V3 (+ by agent)</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Active: They built this house in 1900.</li>
              <li>Passive: This house was built in 1900.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>💬 Reported Speech:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Direct: "I like coffee," she said.</li>
              <li>Reported: She said she liked coffee.</li>
            </ul>`,
            examples: ['Complete the conditionals', 'Transform to passive', 'Change to reported speech'],
